benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/renameKey - Update a bundle externalKey

covered: Valid Request: Happy path tests cover successful update (TC01, TC09, TC14).
Non-Existing Resource: Test covers 404 for nonexistent bundle (TC04).
Concurrency Issues: Test covers concurrent updates to same bundle (TC17).
gaps: Partial Update: No explicit test ensuring partial updates are rejected or only specific fields are updated.
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting/throttling on PUT endpoint.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control).
Authorization boundary: Existing tests touch headers and auth, but explicit token-boundary scenarios could be expanded (TC02/TC12 exist but could be deepened).
recommendations: Add dedicated Partial Update test to validate PUT semantics (whether partial vs full updates are allowed and how extra/missing fields are handled).
Introduce Rate Limiting tests to verify behavior under burst of PUT requests.
Add tests for caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control) to confirm proper caching semantics.
Expand authorization-related test coverage with explicit edge cases (e.g., expired/invalid tokens) to ensure correct 401/403 responses.
